      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "ue_properties": {
          "widget_ue_connectable": {},
          "version": "7.4.1",
          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "  # OmniVoice - TTS Cloning, Voice Design, and Native Timing Control\n\n  OmniVoice is a native multilingual TTS engine that supports both zero-shot voice cloning and reference-free voice design through its instruction field.\n\n  - Use the `📐 Visual Tag Builder` node if you want help composing valid OmniVoice instruction strings\n  - You can also type directly into the engine `instruct` field, but invalid instruction strings may be rejected by the model\n\n  It behaves like any other TTS engine in the suite:\n  connect the Engine to the unified `TTS Text` or `TTS SRT` nodes and generate.\n\n  Officially, OmniVoice supports **600+ languages**.\n\n  It does **not** support `🔄 Voice Changer`.\n\n  OmniVoice supports zero-shot cloning with narrator reference audio, but it requires:\n\n  - reference audio\n  - matching reference text\n\n  So for cloning, prefer the `🎭 Character Voices` node or a narrator voice file with a matching `.reference.txt`.\n  Direct audio-only narrator input is not enough for OmniVoice cloning. If you want to use a direct audio, use a ASR solution first to get the transcription and feed it to `🎭 Character Voices`.\n\n  OmniVoice is also the first engine in the suite with truly useful native duration targeting.\n  Its `duration` and `speed` controls are model-side generation controls, not waveform time-stretch post-processing.\n\n  That makes OmniVoice especially strong for:\n\n  - precise TTS timing\n  - SRT generation\n  - reducing the amount of stretch/compression needed in post timing modes\n\n  OmniVoice also has its own upstream long-form orchestration.\n  It is not a native dialogue engine like VibeVoice, but for long text it uses its official `audio_chunk_duration` and `audio_chunk_threshold` chunking path instead of the suite's normal\n  char-based chunk splitting."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
